<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-44-0572 </DOCNO><TEXT>During interaction of aqueous solutions of cobalt chloride and ammoniummetavanadate at pH of about 6 hydrated cobalt metavanadate is formed.The results of crystallochemical analysis have shown the important roleof water molecules in formation of this structure, their strong relationwith it. Using the method of thermogravimetric analysis it is confirmedthat the object of study is dehydrate.</TEXT></DOC>